  "body_sections": [
    {
      "blocks": [
        {
          "inline": [
            {
              "kind": "text",
              "text": "Return the dot product of two vectors."
            }
          ],
          "type": "paragraph"
        }
      ],
      "title": "Summary"
    },
    {
      "blocks": [
        {
          "inline": [
            {
              "kind": "text",
              "text": "The "
            },
            {
              "external_url": "",
              "href": "/docs/api/ops/vdot",
              "kind": "link",
              "target": "vdot",
              "text": "vdot"
            },
            {
              "kind": "text",
              "text": " function handles complex numbers differently than "
            },
            {
              "external_url": "",
              "href": "/docs/api/ops/dot",
              "kind": "link",
              "target": "dot",
              "text": "dot"
            },
            {
              "kind": "text",
              "text": ":\nif the first argument is complex, it is replaced by its complex conjugate\nin the dot product calculation. "
            },
            {
              "external_url": "",
              "href": "/docs/api/ops/vdot",
              "kind": "link",
              "target": "vdot",
              "text": "vdot"
            },
            {
              "kind": "text",
              "text": " also handles multidimensional\narrays differently than "
            },
            {
              "external_url": "",
              "href": "/docs/api/ops/dot",
              "kind": "link",
              "target": "dot",
              "text": "dot"
            },
            {
              "kind": "text",
              "text": ": it does not perform a matrix product, but\nflattens the arguments to 1-D arrays before taking a vector dot product."
            }
          ],
          "type": "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "inline": [
            {
              "kind": "text",
              "text": "Consequently, when the arguments are 2-D arrays of the same shape, this\nfunction effectively returns their\n"
            },
            {
              "external_url": "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Frobenius_inner_product",
              "href": "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Frobenius_inner_product",
              "kind": "link",
              "text": "Frobenius inner product"
            },
            {
              "kind": "text",
              "text": ""
            },
            {
              "kind": "text",
              "text": "\n(also known as the "
            },
            {
              "kind": "emphasis",
              "text": "trace inner product"
            },
            {
              "kind": "text",
              "text": " or the "
            },
            {
              "kind": "emphasis",
              "text": "standard inner product"
            },
            {
              "kind": "text",
              "text": "\non a vector space of matrices)."
            }
          ],
          "type": "paragraph"
        }
      ],
      "title": "Extended Summary"
    },
    {
      "blocks": [
        {
          "items": [
            {
              "body_blocks": [
                {
                  "inline": [
                    {
                      "kind": "text",
                      "text": "If "
                    },
                    {
                      "kind": "code",
                      "text": "a"
                    },
                    {
                      "kind": "text",
                      "text": " is complex the complex conjugate is taken before calculation\nof the dot product."
                    }
                  ],
                  "type": "paragraph"
                }
              ],
              "data_type": "array_like",
